         <div type="traslation">
            <head>Translation</head>
      <ab>On the day of the year Sarvadhāri, month Puraṭhāśi, 25th day, Wednesday, of the new moon of the dark fortnight of the month of Bhādrapada (mākāḷayapakṣa), the seventh (yeṣā) section was fully copied. May there be prosperity; this manuscript is the manuscript of Kāvaśeri Sundaraśāstrikaḷ.
               
         <lg> 
            <l>As I saw in the manuscript, thus I copied it,</l>
               <l>whether nonsensical or meaningful. No fault is mine.</l>
               <l>Visargas, nasal signs, morae, and words, lines, syllables:</l>
               <l>may Parameśvarī forgive whether there are too few (nyūnāniś emend. nyūnāni) or too many.</l>
               
            </lg>
               
      </ab>  
